args:
As Dyrenell's forces strike again, Nefaria
recalls her death in the defense of her subjects.
Now returned from beyond the veil, she swears
to stake her life on keeping her people safe
once more, and Horus grants her the means.
Ugh, these guys have ZERO chill!\nHow are we supposed to enjoy a festival\nwhen they're all up in our biz?
We must halt their advance at all cost.
(This pain again... Battle drives my head\nto split ever since I met that dragon.)
(Memories of war flood my mind,\nbut why? What are these ill fantasies?)
W-worry not, I am well. And thank you.
Ria, come with me. Right now.
Yep—and it's where you're\ngonna stay put.
Have your senses fled you?\nMy place is ever at the fore!
You're not exactly in fighting shape.\nGirl, you look ROUGH.
Are you hurt somewhere? Like, maybe one\nof those ＂I'm super bleeding internally but\ndon't wanna make it a thing＂ things?
Okay, did I not JUST finish telling you\nthat I've got your back?
I'm not just gonna stand around\nand watch my best friend suffer.
Whatever scantling of pain I may feel\nis inconsequential.
I am queen of the Sandreach. Though my\nkingdom be fallen, the defense of her\npeople is ever my onus to bear.
Even if it kills you?! Like, AGAIN?!
Ah! Um, so I didn't meeean...
Pray what DID you mean, Nadine?
If you hold a secret in your heart,\nI would have you discover it to me now.
I guess keeping it bottled up would only\nmake things worse or whatever...
Prithee, Nadine. If you know aught\nof my demise, I would fain hear it.

Okay, so the Sandreach was invaded
by the Empire centuries back and was
wiped out. That's what everybody
taught us, anyway.
And the only reason us dunefolk survived\nwas because the queen protected us. But...
Ria, that's WHY she died.\nShe died trying to save us all.
Hurry Her Majesty to safety!\nPermit the Empire no further advance!
My Queen, do not leave us!
Heed me, good subjects...\nFor my final hour is at hand...
No! We'll not allow this, My Queen!\nYour finest healers speed here even now!
I know my body well... I am lost.
Now hearken to my final order...\nCast your kingdom aside...and live...
I shall not suffer my people to follow me\nin death, nor live their lives 'neath\nDyrenell's cruel boot.
Which is why you must forsake this land.\nLive free...and ever cherish your fellows.
I wish only for my people's joy...\nSo pray live out your days with a smile\nupon your faces...
Know that no happier queen e'er lived,\nfor I am blessed by my people's love.\nI bear...no regrets...
I remember now. The day I perished...\nI remember it all.
Look, I know it might be a queen's job to\nkeep her people safe and stuff. I mean,\nI guess that's what's ＂right.＂
But I don't want my friend to die!
I'm so sorry, Ria! I promised I'd help you\nfind your memories, but I was keeping this\nsecret the whole time.
I was worried you'd go do something\nwhackadoodle if you remembered it now.\nI'm really, REALLY sorry.
Nay, Nadine. 'Tis I must ask forgiveness;\nI should have begged your help sooner\nrather than cause strife and mischief.
Besides, you have led me to my answer.
Whoa?! Whoa, wait. Like, WHOA!\nWho the heck is that?!
Ah, Horus. An opportune appearance;\nI recall you now, as well.
Horus... Wait, you mean THE Horus?\nThe dragon who's in charge of the\nSandreach's royal line and junk?!
Indeed, I am he who planted the seed\nof a nation in these vast dunes.
I would ask you once more, Nefaria:\nDoes a queen unmade for love of her\nsubjects yet cling to that love in death?
T'was not the love I hold for my people\nthat killed me, Horus. My weakness alone\nmust bear that fell honor.
Was sacrificing your life and loving your\npeople not one and the same to you?
Was it love that led me to spurn the feelings\nof those left behind?
Such is weakness, not love—and it was\nweakness claimed my life that day.
Love had no hand in my death, and so\nbears no guilt today. I've no cause not to\nlove my people still with all that I am.
Then will you fight without fear\nfor your people once more?
Aye, without hesitation—though I shall\nnot repeat my folly.
I am not alone now as I was then.\nThis day, I am graced with a boon\ncompanion at my side.
Where one soon falls, two stand firm,\neach bolstered by the other.
I can think of naught so powerful as\nfriendship. Though I am weak, I shall don\nit as my armor and wield it as my sword.
Nadine, will you fight beside me as I\nseek to spare the people I...
No. This time, I seek not to spare them,\nbut to live on together WITH them.
Then a monarch would seek an equal?\nBut is it not a ruler's place to stand atop\ntheir flock instead of mingled within?
Your answer is illogical. Inscrutable.\nI find your actions beyond my ken.
Then lend me now your power, Horus!
Do this, and I shall show you firsthand\nthe answers you now lack.
Then I would observe with my own eyes\nwhat use the revenant queen would put\nmy power to.
Whoa, this Horus guy is no joke...\nHis mana is HOT FIRE!
To me, Nadine! To me, Horus!\nThis day, we let slip the dogs of war!
